description: Try our easy to follow Leftover Veggie Frittata recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Leftover Veggie Frittata Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat grill to high. Heat oil in a 20cm non-stick frying pan over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and fry for 3–4 minutes or until softened. Add vegetables and stir to combine. Cook, stirring often, for 2–3 minutes or until all the vegetables are heated through. Remove from heat.
Whisk eggs and cream together in a bowl. Add cheese and parsley. Season with salt and pepper.

Return pan to heat. Pour in egg mixture, covering the vegetables, and cook for 8 minutes or until base is set. Transfer to the grill for 5 minutes or until puffed and golden. Cut into squares and serve.
